# ===== Instructions =====
# 
# 1. Create R2 bucket:
#    wrangler r2 bucket create zero-dash-builds
# 
# 2. Enable public access:
#    Cloudflare Dashboard → R2 → zero-dash-builds → Settings → Public Access
# 
# 3. Create API token:
#    Cloudflare Dashboard → R2 → Manage R2 API Tokens → Create API Token
#    Permissions: Read & Write for your bucket
# 
# 4. Copy this file:
#    cp .env.example .env
# 
# 5. Fill in your values in .env
# 
# 6. Test upload:
#    npm run upload:latest
# 
# ===== Security Notes =====
# 
# - NEVER commit .env to git!
# - .env is already in .gitignore
# - Store secrets in GitHub Secrets for CI/CD
# - Rotate keys if accidentally exposed
